main event: A bright light was observed hovering and moving over Sheboygan, Wisconsin on March 24, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to split into two objects before coming back together and hovering in one spot for about 10 minutes.
The object suddenly shot straight up at a very fast speed and disappeared from view.
The witness estimated the object was approximately 20-30 feet in diameter and 100-150 feet high.
Another witness reported seeing a large airplane-like craft with unusual glowing lights in the same area on the same night.
The witness felt they may have seen this type of craft before but couldn't remember where.
sighted object: a bright light that appeared to be a hovering disc-shaped craft
